# Operational Model

## Governance Model
Andamio enables organizations to build localized governance systems while maintaining interoperability through shared credential standards and on-chain verification. The platform supports credential-gated governance participation and treasury coordination. :contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}

## Maintenance Model
The platform appears to be maintained through a hybrid model consisting of:
- Open source repositories
- Core development teams
- Ecosystem funding
- API and platform infrastructure operations

## Funding Model
- Ecosystem grants
- Treasury funding
- API infrastructure services
- Enterprise integrations
- Hosted platform services

## Contributor Model
Contributors can:
- Earn verifiable credentials
- Build interoperable applications
- Participate in governance systems
- Contribute through project-based workflows
- Carry portable on-chain work history between applications

